Hereâ€™s a list of commonly used Linux commands, categorized for easy reference:

---

### ðŸ”¹ **Basic File and Directory Commands**

| Command        | Description                          |
| -------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| `ls`           | List directory contents              |
| `cd`           | Change directory                     |
| `pwd`          | Show current directory path          |
| `mkdir`        | Create a new directory               |
| `rmdir`        | Remove an empty directory            |
| `rm`           | Delete files or directories          |
| `cp`           | Copy files or directories            |
| `mv`           | Move or rename files                 |
| `touch`        | Create an empty file                 |
| `cat`          | Display file contents                |
| `more`, `less` | View file contents page-by-page      |
| `find`         | Search for files and directories     |
| `locate`       | Quickly find files (uses a database) |

---

### ðŸ”¹ **File Permissions and Ownership**

| Command | Description             |
| ------- | ----------------------- |
| `chmod` | Change file permissions |
| `chown` | Change file owner       |
| `chgrp` | Change group ownership  |

---

### ðŸ”¹ **System Information**

| Command       | Description             |
| ------------- | ----------------------- |
| `uname -a`    | Show system information |
| `top`, `htop` | Show running processes  |
| `df -h`       | Show disk space usage   |
| `du -sh`      | Show directory size     |
| `free -h`     | Show memory usage       |
| `uptime`      | Show system uptime      |
| `whoami`      | Show current user       |

---

### ðŸ”¹ **Process Management**

| Command     | Description                       |
| ----------- | --------------------------------- |
| `ps`        | Show running processes            |
| `kill`      | Kill a process by PID             |
| `killall`   | Kill a process by name            |
| `bg` / `fg` | Run jobs in background/foreground |
| `jobs`      | Show background jobs              |

---

### ðŸ”¹ **Networking**

| Command             | Description                         |
| ------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| `ping`              | Test network connection             |
| `ifconfig` / `ip a` | Show IP address info                |
| `netstat -tuln`     | Show open ports                     |
| `ssh user@host`     | Connect to remote server            |
| `scp`               | Securely copy files between systems |
| `curl` / `wget`     | Download files from web             |

---

### ðŸ”¹ **Package Management (Debian/Ubuntu)**

| Command       | Description         |
| ------------- | ------------------- |
| `apt update`  | Update package list |
| `apt upgrade` | Upgrade packages    |
| `apt install` | Install a package   |
| `apt remove`  | Remove a package    |

---

### ðŸ”¹ **Archive and Compression**

| Command                         | Description                  |
| ------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| `tar -czvf file.tar.gz folder/` | Create a compressed archive  |
| `tar -xzvf file.tar.gz`         | Extract a compressed archive |
| `zip -r file.zip folder/`       | Create a zip archive         |
| `unzip file.zip`                | Extract a zip archive        |

---

### ðŸ”¹ **Other Useful Commands**

| Command   | Description                    |
| --------- | ------------------------------ |
| `history` | Show command history           |
| `alias`   | Create shortcuts for commands  |
| `man`     | Show manual page for a command |
| `echo`    | Display a line of text         |
| `date`    | Show current date and time     |
| `clear`   | Clear terminal screen          |

